  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">AWD/Cholera Emergency Response in Gedo &amp; Middle Juba Regions</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">RI delivers an intervention for AWD/Cholaera both in terms of prevention (predominanly through WASH) and support of increasced curative/clinical care and treatment. Curative interventions take place in Middle Juba (Saakow and Bu&apos;aale districts) and Gedo (Belet Hawa district) with preventative and sensitization activities in Gedo (Baardhere). These services include procurement, transportation and supply to Cholera Treatment Centers (CTCs) critical supplies necessary for treatment of patients (oral rehydration salts (ORS) and IV fluids, ringer lactate, tetracycline, zinc and Aquatabs) in Saakow, Bu&apos;aale and Belet Hawa. In Baardhere, the Somalia WASH Cluster provides in-kind supplies of hygiene kits, which include Aquatabs for purifying water for drinking, jerry cans, 20 liter buckets and soap with hygiene promotion campaigns.  RI also coordinates with SRCS and the Health Cluster to ensure disease monitoring data is fed back to maintain an overview of the spread of AWD/Cholera, including if new cases are identified.</narrative>
  </description>
